<br />
<strong>About MODXpo</strong><br />
MODXpo is the official, international MODX user conference. MODX developers, designers and site builders gather to learn, share, explore and network. Our first MODXpo was held in Dallas, in 2010 and <a href="http://modxpo.eu/2012/home" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">last year</a> was held in the city of Utrecht in the Netherlands. If you&#039;ve not been to a MODXpo, this is the event for you.<br />
<br />
<strong>MODXpo 2013 Highlights</strong><br />
There are top-notch keynotes, presentations, workshops, and much more, from well known MODX community members including Susan Ottwell, Mark Hamstra and Gauke Pieter Sietzema. Ryan Thrash, MODX Co-founder, will present his State of MODX and showcase the past, present and future of MODX. Other great sessions include: responsive development tools, continuous deployment, scaling and high availability, how not to build MODX sites, case studies, contributing to MODX and much more. In addition, there will be plenty of time for making connections and code.<br />
<br />
<strong>More Info</strong><br />
For complete details including the <a href="http://2013.modxpo.eu/schedule" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">schedule</a>, <a href="http://2013.modxpo.eu/location" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">location</a> and more, please go to <a href="http://2013.modxpo.eu" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">2013.modxpo.eu</a>. <br />
